      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Lots of win chances. DEMIQUAVER (6) is fitter for two runs back and looks ready to find winning form. Well placed here with a drop in class and also weight and building a good record here. Gets chance. SCISSOR ME TIMBERS (8) was in great form but settled further back than usual last time and made good late ground but never threatened. This is easier and expected to take catching. MOUGENOT (3) was below his best last time out when 7 lengths from the winner in seventh here over 1000m. Record at this track is strong. Has the ability and can bounce back. HELLIVIT (10) was a winner over 1100m at Tennant Creek last time out, dropping out early before coming home with a powerful run to score by a long neck. Strong record this course and distance and drawn to figure in the finish. ZESTIMAN (4) is also back in form and worth following up. Chances don't end there.",
